<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/123710279-aurora">Aurora</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Well, it’s not been easy for me to read it as native Italian speaker, because it has a lot of words that are not written as they are today and some wo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Well, it’s not been easy for me to read it as native Italian speaker, because it has a lot of words that are not written as they are today and some words and verbs are not easy and are not used nowadays. However, if your goal is to practice Italian by reading one of the best book (in my opinion) in Italian literature without understanding each word but the content I think you could give it a try! <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
