<div id="review_687878454" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/687878454" />
    <a title="Nicholas During" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/440220-nicholas-during"><img alt="Nicholas During" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1306953644p2/440220.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/687878454?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nicholas During" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nicholas During" href="/user/show/440220-nicholas-during">Nicholas During</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer687878454" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18405414084036500379">What would happen if everyone you knew thought you were dead? Would you rejoice in a newfound liberty of a new, fresh life? Away from that boring wife? The reduced wealth of you family? The insults of your neighbors that you can&apos;t fight? That&apos;s what happens to Mattia Pascal. But of course nothing really works out like we plan in this world unfortunately. And it turns out complete freedom from everything has its costs too. Try travelling without a passport. And more than that, even if circumstanc</span>
  <span id="freeText18405414084036500379" style="display:none">What would happen if everyone you knew thought you were dead? Would you rejoice in a newfound liberty of a new, fresh life? Away from that boring wife? The reduced wealth of you family? The insults of your neighbors that you can't fight? That's what happens to Mattia Pascal. But of course nothing really works out like we plan in this world unfortunately. And it turns out complete freedom from everything has its costs too. Try travelling without a passport. And more than that, even if circumstances are absolutely changed, could we change our personality? Our characteristics? People who read self-help books often think they can, but I think I may agree with Pirandello that it's not as easy as it sounds. Not that this means we should always stay where we are. Sometimes the only way to learn a lesson is to make a mistake, to lose something, to realize that our dreams are impossible. This may not bring happiness, but a sensible understanding of reality, and its absurdity, might be the only thing we can ask for. And what better way to explore the absurd situations that is reality than in fiction. God knows it makes it a bit more interesting too. Keep your eyes open.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18405414084036500379" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


