    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1527605111" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1527605111" />
    <a title="Alex" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52016563-alex"><img alt="Alex" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1527605111?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alex" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alex" href="/user/show/52016563-alex">Alex</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52016563-alex?shelf=existence-as-trap">existence-as-trap</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52016563-alex?shelf=melted-nobel-medal">melted-nobel-medal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52016563-alex?shelf=postmodern-over-reliance-on-play">postmodern-over-reliance-on-play</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1527605111" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5631429352736285045"><p>Pascal is mistakenly declared dead, and he takes advantage by abandoning his life for a new one. Much later, when others discover his actions, everyone approves. Why return when the opportunity exists to leave?<br/></p><p>Every existence is a prison. To leave one life means to take up another, and taking up this other life means taking up its shackles. Pascal tries to avoid commitments and requirements, but the avoidance of commitment shackles him as well.<br/></p><p>The Late Mattia Pascal could be read as a deeply con</p></span>
  <span id="freeText5631429352736285045" style="display:none"><p>Pascal is mistakenly declared dead, and he takes advantage by abandoning his life for a new one. Much later, when others discover his actions, everyone approves. Why return when the opportunity exists to leave?<br /></p><p>Every existence is a prison. To leave one life means to take up another, and taking up this other life means taking up its shackles. Pascal tries to avoid commitments and requirements, but the avoidance of commitment shackles him as well.<br /></p><p>The Late Mattia Pascal could be read as a deeply conservative text. (The author did, after all, send his Nobel medal to Mussolini for melting down to its gold.) Movement seems to be discouraged, as Pascal finally rejects his attempts at new life to take up the yoke of his old one again. But the energy of the tale counters Pascal's conclusions. An adventure has been had, and if he found no transcendance or deliverance, all parties have at least managed diversion. In this aspect Pirandello anticipates the postmodern reliance on play.</p></span>
  <a data-text-id="5631429352736285045" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

